      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Empirical evidence from past tax cuts, such as the 2017 Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, has shown a very mixed and often disappointing trickle-down effect. Studies consistently demonstrate that the majority of the benefits from corporate and high-income tax reductions flow to the wealthiest segments of society, not the working class. The theory of trickle-down economics is largely a political talking point that lacks robust, consistent empirical backing when examining real-world distributional outcomes.",
